CRITICAL BUGS (will crash or silently break core functionality)
================================================================

#1: Missing `await` on async function applyReversibleCompression
  File: src/index.ts:162-165
  Bug:  const reversible = applyReversibleCompression(filtered)
  Fix:  const reversible = await applyReversibleCompression(filtered)
  Impact: L20 reversible compression for bash outputs is completely dead.
          reversible is a Promise, .compressed is always undefined → condition never true.

#2: Plugin API type mismatch — ToolInput.args doesn't exist in SDK
  File: src/index.ts:54-57, 370
  Bug:  interface ToolInput { tool: string; args: Record<string, unknown> }
        But @opencode-ai/plugin's tool.execute.before hook passes:
        { tool: string; sessionID: string; callID: string } — no args field.
  Fix:  Match actual SDK interface.
  Impact: Plugin registration will fail type check. Runtime behavior depends on SDK version.

#3: process.env.HOME crashes at module evaluation time in Bun
  File: src/lspfirst.ts:12
  Bug:  const LSP_STATE_DIR = process.env.HOME + "/.config/opentoken/lsp"
        process is a Node.js global, undefined in Bun by default.
  Fix:  Use os.homedir() like every other module in this project.
  Impact: ReferenceError at import time → plugin never loads.

#4: Bun.$([cmd]) array syntax is invalid (9+ locations)
  Files:
    src/progressive.ts:29, 144
    src/rewind.ts:159, 184
    src/symbolindex.ts:223, 341, 369
    src/skeleton.ts:351
    src/sandbox.ts:66, 294
  Bug:  await Bun.$([`mkdir -p ${OFFLOAD_DIR}`]).quiet()
        Bun.$ expects a tagged template literal, not an array.
  Fix:  Use template literal: await Bun.$`mkdir -p ${OFFLOAD_DIR}`.quiet()
  Impact: All shell commands silently no-op. Directory creation, file deletion,
          find execution, sandbox execution all broken.

#5: Undefined variable codeBlock in markdown filter
  File: src/filters/read.ts:68
  Bug:  codeBlock = 0
        line 62 declares codeBlockLines. The variable codeBlock does not exist.
  Fix:  Change to codeBlockLines = 0
  Impact: ReferenceError crashes read filter when processing .md files with code blocks.

HIGH BUGS (cause wrong behavior / silent data loss / security issues)
====================================================================

#6: Duplicate keys in object literals (27+ locations) — silent data loss
  Files:
    src/utils/abbreviate.ts:23,45,82,99-100,112,114,116,122,125-126,136,
                             148,150,152,154,156,159-160,162,164-166,171-178
    src/autoescalate.ts:117-119
  Bug:  Duplicate keys in ABBREVIATIONS and synonyms objects.
        JS keeps the LAST value silently. E.g.:
          "functionality": "feature"     // line 117
          "functionality": "features"    // line 118 — overwrites
          "temporary": "tmp"             // line 44
          "temporary": "temp"            // line 45 — overwrites with different value!
  Fix:  Remove all duplicate keys, keep canonical mapping.
  Impact: Wrong abbreviations applied silently. Some words get unexpected replacements.

#7: Cache stores original content, not filtered
  File: src/index.ts:254
  Bug:  await setCachedRead(filePath, content)
        content is the unfiltered original. filtered is the compressed result.
  Fix:  await setCachedRead(filePath, filtered)
  Impact: Second read bypasses entire compression pipeline. Returns full original.

#8: Cached read returns summary string, not content
  File: src/index.ts:194
  Bug:  return `[Cached read: ${filePath} — ${cached.split("\n").length} lines]`
        Returns a summary message instead of the cached content. The next stage
        gets this short message as the "file content" and only this enters context.
  Fix:  Return the actual cached content directly.
  Impact: After first read, all subsequent reads of the same file return a
          1-line summary. The LLM never sees the file content on cached reads.

#9: Object.assign on possibly undefined output.args
  File: src/index.ts:380
  Bug:  Object.assign(output.args, result.modifiedArgs)
        output.args is typed as Record<string, unknown> | undefined.
  Fix:  Object.assign(output.args ??= {}, result.modifiedArgs)
  Impact: TypeError crash when output.args is undefined.

#10: Context tracking replaces instead of accumulates
  File: src/autoescalate.ts:32
  Bug:  state.contextUsed = used   // overwrites, not accumulates
        Called from index.ts:457 as updateContext(beforeTokens) — each call
        replaces the running total with the last call's token count.
  Fix:  state.contextUsed += used
  Impact: Auto-escalation compression level is based on the last call only,
          not cumulative context fill. Never escalates properly.

#11: Shell injection in sandbox scripts (6 locations)
  File: src/sandbox.ts:129,150,169,191,213,233
  Bug:  for file in ${files.join(" ")}; do
        File paths are interpolated unquoted into generated bash scripts.
  Fix:  Quote variables: for file in "${files[@]}"; do
  Impact: File paths with spaces or shell metacharacters enable code execution.

#12: Shell injection in find command
  File: src/symbolindex.ts:222
  Bug:  const cmd = `find ${dirPath} -type f ...
        dirPath interpolated unquoted into shell command string.
  Fix:  Use Bun.spawn(["find", dirPath, ...args]) with proper arg array.
  Impact: Project paths with spaces break the symbol index. Metacharacters
          enable injection.

#13: skeleton.ts return type mismatch
  File: src/skeleton.ts:258-260
  Bug:  function extractSkeletonRegex(content: string, language: string): string {
          const config = PATTERN_LOOKUP[language]
          if (!config) return null   // can't return null from a string function
  Fix:  Change return type to string | null (caller already handles null).
  Impact: TypeScript compilation error. Runtime may return null unexpectedly.

#14: Metrics ensureDir writes empty file to directory path
  File: src/utils/metrics.ts:17-19
  Bug:  async function ensureDir() {
          await Bun.file(METRICS_DIR).exists() || await Bun.write(METRICS_DIR, "")
        METRICS_DIR is a directory path. Bun.write to a directory creates a
        regular file at the directory path, destroying the directory.
  Fix:  Use Bun.$`mkdir -p ${METRICS_DIR}`.quiet()
  Impact: ~/.config/opentoken directory gets replaced by an empty file.
          All subsequent file operations (metrics, session, rewind, etc.) fail.

#15: cleanWhitespaceAndNulls produces invalid JSON (double commas)
  File: src/postcall.ts:222-235
  Bug:  Multiple stripping regexes remove ,"key":value patterns by replacing
        with "". When two adjacent fields are stripped, the result is:
          {"a": 1, , "b": 2}   ← invalid JSON
        The trailing comma cleanup (lines 238-241) handles ,} and ,] but
        NOT double commas.
  Fix:  result = result.replace(/,(\s*,)+/g, ",") after all stripping passes.
  Impact: JSON output can become syntactically invalid. LLM may misparse.

#16: aliasJsonKeys corrupts string values
  File: src/postcall.ts:185
  Bug:  return text.replace(/"([a-zA-Z_]\w*)"\s*:/g, ...)
        Matches "word": patterns anywhere, including inside string values.
        E.g. {"msg": "the description is here"} → {"msg": "the desc is here"}
  Fix:  Use a proper JSON parser or restrict to key positions only.
  Impact: String content gets corrupted. False key aliasing.

#17: Find code files uses shell find instead of FS API
  File: src/symbolindex.ts:220-224
  Bug:  Shell injection via dirPath (same as #12). Also the fallback glob
        handler (line 226) is empty — silently returns empty array.
  Fix:  Implement the glob fallback or use Bun's glob API.
  Impact: Symbol index silently indexes nothing if find fails.

#18: JSonsample string replacement fragility
  File: src/jsonsample.ts:179
  Bug:  result = result.replace(arrayStr, `${summary}\n${sampledStr}`)
        arrayStr is JSON.stringify(items). If the array appears multiple times
        in the content (same items appearing at different nesting levels),
        only the first match is replaced. If the array appears zero times
        (because JSON.stringify produced different whitespace than source),
        no replacement happens.
  Fix:  Parse, modify, re-stringify. Or use a structural traversal.
  Impact: JSON sampling silently fails for objects with large arrays.

#19: aliasJsonKeys output/input map to same alias but different keys
  File: src/postcall.ts:110-117
  Bug:  "output": "out", "outputs": "outs", "input": "in", "inputs": "ins"
        Map entries use the same alias for different keys:
          "out" maps to both "output" and "outs" (in some contexts)
          "input" → "in" collides with JavaScript keyword "in"
  Fix:  Disambiguate: "output"→"out", "outputs"→"outs", "input"→"inp", "inputs"→"inps"
  Impact: Lossy key aliasing where multiple keys collapse to the same alias.

#20: Error tracking uses filtered output, not original
  File: src/index.ts:171-173
  Bug:  if (hasErrors(output)) { trackError(filtered.slice(0, 200)) }
        hasErrors checks original output, but trackError gets filtered content.
        If filtering removed error indicators, the stored error is misleading.
  Fix:  trackError(output.slice(0, 200))
  Impact: Session memory stores potentially wrong error summaries.

#21: key_alias regex collision with output aliasing
  File: src/postcall.ts:185-191
  Bug:  Same regex replaces JSON keys AND values. If LONG_KEY_MAP has both
        "output": "out" and "outputs": "outs", the regex for "output" fires
        first on "outputs" because matching is greedy. "outputs" → "outs"
        is never reached. Actually, the regex matches "outputs" as a whole
        key — but LONG_KEY_MAP["outputs"] = "outs", so it works. However
        if the longer key is not in the map, the shorter prefix key fires.
  Fix:  Sort keys by length descending before matching.
  Impact: Non-deterministic key aliasing when keys are prefixes of each other.

#22: progressive.ts uses AND instead of OR for offload threshold
  File: src/progressive.ts:81
  Bug:  if (lines.length <= MAX_INLINE_LINES && content.length <= MAX_INLINE_BYTES)
        Both conditions must be true to skip offload. Content with 150 lines
        but 25KB (under line limit, over byte limit) still offloads.
  Fix:  Change && to || if intent is "skip offload if under either threshold"
        OR keep && if both must be under (current behavior — just verifying).
  Impact: More content gets offloaded than necessary, increasing disk I/O.

#23: git.ts status regex too strict
  File: src/families/git.ts:34
  Bug:  /^[AMDRCU?!\s]{2}\s+/
        The \s inside [] matches space. Standard git short status uses
        space as the first character for unmodified index. But some
        git configurations may use different indicators. Also this
        doesn't match "?? " (untracked) format correctly.
  Fix:  Widen regex to handle all git status formats.
  Impact: Some git status outputs may not be parsed correctly.

#24: router.ts log detection regex anchor issue
  File: src/router.ts:73
  Bug:  /^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}|\[INFO\]|\[WARN\]|\[ERROR\]/
        The ^ only anchors the date pattern, not the bracketed patterns.
        "[INFO]" anywhere in content triggers "log" classification.
  Fix:  /(?:^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}|^\[INFO\]|^\[WARN\]|^\[ERROR\])/m
  Impact: Any content containing [INFO] anywhere is treated as log output,
          triggering log folding. False positives on normal text.

#25: removeZeroValues removes valid data
  File: src/postcall.ts:201
  Bug:  /,\s*"[^"]*"\s*:\s*0(?![\d.])/g
        Removes {"count": 0, "total": 0} — zero values that may be meaningful.
  Fix:  Only strip null/empty, not zero.
  Impact: Loss of semantically meaningful zero values in JSON.

#26: UUID pattern too broad — removes debugging IDs
  File: src/postcall.ts:210
  Bug:  /,\s*"(id|uuid|_id|oid)"\s*:\s*"[a-f0-9-]{20,}"/g
        Removes all IDs with 20+ hex chars. These may be needed for debugging.
  Fix:  Make configurable. Only strip if the engine knows IDs aren't needed.
  Impact: Debugging information silently lost.

#27: Diff folding context replacement loses info
  File: src/folding.ts:44-53
  Bug:  Short context runs (≤3 lines) replaced with "  [context]" placeholder.
        The actual context content is lost.
  Fix:  Keep short context runs as-is, only fold runs >3.
  Impact: Meaningful context lines near changes are discarded.

#28: dedup.ts comparison threshold uses truncated content
  File: src/dedup.ts:53-58, 69
  Bug:  Jaccard similarity compares full passed content against stored first
        200 chars. Two outputs that share same first 200 chars but differ
        significantly after will match as "similar" (if Jaccard > 0.85).
  Fix:  Store full content for comparison, or increase stored chunk, or
        use rolling hash.
  Impact: Potential false dedup dedup for outputs with same prefix.

