#32: countTokens always falls back to estimateTokens
  File: src/utils/tokens.ts:23-27
  Bug:  async function countTokens(text: string): Promise<number> {
          const tokenizer = await getTokenizer()
          const tokens = tokenizer.encode(text)
          return tokens.length || estimateTokens(text)
        }
        getTokenizer imports @anthropic-ai/tokenizer which is not in
        package.json dependencies. import always throws, _tokenizer gets
        set to { encode: () => [] }, encode returns []. tokens.length
        is 0, falls back to estimateTokens.
  Fix:  Add @anthropic-ai/tokenizer as optional dependency, or remove
        the dead code path.
  Impact: Exact token counting never works as documented.

#33: Get function source returns wrong content on method overloads
  File: src/symbolindex.ts:261-262
  Bug:  return lines.slice(symbol.line - 1, symbol.line + 49).join("\n")
        Always returns 50 lines regardless of where the function ends.
        For overloaded methods or multiple declarations on adjacent lines,
        this includes nearby unrelated code.
  Fix:  Implement brace counting to find actual function end.
  Impact: get_function_source returns imprecise results.

#34: Abbreviate doesn't handle word boundaries correctly
  File: src/utils/abbreviate.ts:202-203
  Bug:  const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${full}\\b`, "gi")
        Some entries in ABBREVIATIONS are multi-word phrases requiring
        different handling. "asynchronous" matches "asynchronously" prefix
        then replaces with "async" leaving "ly" — producing "asynonly".
  Fix:  Ensure regex matches only exact words, not word prefixes.
  Impact: Partial word replacement produces wrong text.

#35: Progress bars and spinner output not filtered
  File: src/families/generic.ts (no handling)
  Bug:  Generic filter does head+tail truncation. Progress bar output
        (npm install spinner, cargo compilation lines) passes through.
  Fix:  Add pattern to strip \r-based progress lines and spinner chars.
  Impact: Progress spinners and \r-update lines waste tokens.

#36: Session memory project matching is too strict
  File: src/session.ts:76
  Bug:  if (project && summary.project !== project) return null
        Project comparison is exact string match. Running from /home/user/proj
        vs /home/user/proj/ (trailing slash) won't match.
  Fix:  Normalize paths before comparison.
  Impact: Cross-session memory only works if paths match exactly.

#37: Rewind cleanup uses rm -f instead of Bun API
  File: src/rewind.ts:159
  Bug:  await Bun.$([`rm -f ${filePath}`]).quiet()
        Inconsistent API usage. Also susceptible to #4 (array bug) and
        shell injection via filePath.
  Fix:  Use await Bun.file(filePath).delete() or Bun.write(filePath, "")
  Impact: File deletion fails silently (due to #4). Temp files accumulate.

#38: createAnalysisScript returns scriptPath as "" for all built-in scripts
  File: src/sandbox.ts:139,158,179,202,225,244
  Bug:  return { script, scriptPath: "", description: ... }
        scriptPath is always empty string. executeSandbox can't find the file.
        These scripts are never actually executed.
  Fix:  Write script to file before returning path, or remove the unsued
        execution path.
  Impact: Smart analysis scripts are generated but never run.

#39: No test coverage for main pipeline orchestration
  File: tests/opentoken.test.ts
  Bug:  applyBashFilter, applyReadFilter, applyGrepFilter, applyGlobFilter,
        OpenTokenPlugin — zero tests for the main pipeline functions.
        5 out of 24 layers have no meaningful test coverage.
  Fix:  Add integration tests for pipeline orchestration.
  Impact: Refactoring risk. Pipeline bugs not caught by tests.

#40: No integration test coverage for OpenTokenPlugin lifecycle
  File: tests/opentoken.test.ts
  Bug:  The plugin itself is never instantiated or tested. No test verifies
        that hooks register, fire, or interact correctly.
  Fix:  Add plugin lifecycle tests.
  Impact: Entire plugin may fail in production without test detection.

#41: Empty catch blocks everywhere — zero observability
  Files: Throughout the codebase (30+ locations)
  Bug:  Each try/catch has an empty catch block (// Ignore, // Silent fail).
        There is no logging, no metrics recording, no error propagation.
  Fix:  Add structured logging or metrics recording in catch blocks.
  Impact: All failures are invisible. Debugging in production is impossible.

#42: Configuration system described in README but never implemented
  File: README.md:74-91
  Bug:  README documents ~config.json with cache_ttl_seconds, max_lines_short_output,
        etc. None of these are actually read by the code. All values are
        hardcoded constants.
  Fix:  Implement config loading or remove from README.
  Impact: Documentation lies to users. Configuration changes have no effect.

#43: Package.json main points to .ts source, not compiled output
  File: package.json:6
  Bug:  "main": "src/index.ts"
        tsconfig builds to dist/. There's no build script either.
  Fix:  Point to dist/index.js and add a build script.
  Impact: Unclear whether runtime expects .ts or .js.

#44: Bun.$(["cmd"]) creates subprocess with wrong args
  File: src/sandbox.ts:66
  Bug:  const result = await Bun.$([cmd]).quiet()
        When Bun.$ gets an array, it passes the array elements as argv,
        but the first element is the entire command string. The kernel
        treats the whole string as the executable path, which fails with
        ENOENT (no such file "bash script.py").
  Impact: Sandbox execution always fails. No scripts are ever run.

#45: rust and go sandbox scripts are stubs
  File: src/sandbox.ts:282-288
  Bug:  fn main() { println!("Rust sandbox not yet implemented"); }
        func main() { fmt.Println("Go sandbox not yet implemented"); }
  Fix:  Implement or remove.
  Impact: Feature parity claim is false.

#46: LSP state uses process.env without fallback
  File: src/lspfirst.ts:12
  Bug:  const LSP_STATE_DIR = process.env.HOME + "/.config/opentoken/lsp"
        No fallback if process or process.env.HOME is undefined.
  Fix:  Use os.homedir() from 'node:os'.
  Impact: Crash at module scope (duplicate of #3 with added severity).

#47: cleanWhitespaceAndNulls skips if input has no {} even when content is JSON array
  File: src/postcall.ts:218
  Bug:  if (!text.includes("{") || !text.includes("}")) return text
        A JSON array [{"key":"val"}] contains {} so it passes. But a plain
        array ["a","b"] would be skipped.
  Fix:  Check for [ and ] as well.
  Impact: Array-only JSON outputs skip whitespace cleanup.

#48: Session memory filesTouched uses Set but getSessionTracker creates a new Set
  File: src/session.ts:188-190, 216-226
  Bug:  trackFile adds to the singleton tracker. getSessionTracker creates
        a new Set from the singleton. This is actually correct (defensive copy).
        But finalizeSession passes tracker.filesTouched (the Set) to
        saveSessionSummary which expects filesTouched: string[].
        Set<string> is not string[]. JSON.stringify converts Set to {}.
  Fix:  [...tracker.filesTouched] in finalizeSession.
  Impact: Session memory stores {} for files touched instead of the actual list.
